New Records: Cleveland Cavaliers became the 12th team in NBA history to start a season 11-0
Key Match Events: Cleveland Cavaliers trailed 82-68 with 35 seconds left in the third quarter before rallying for the win
Darius Garland scored eight of his 20 points in the fourth quarter to give the Cavaliers the lead
The Cavaliers failed to score 110 points, ending their NBA-record streak of doing so in 10 consecutive wins to open a season
Miscellaneous Highlights: The 2015-16 Golden State Warriors hold the league record after winning their first 24 games.
Cam Johnson scored 23 points and Dennis Schroder and Cam Thomas had 22 apiece for the Nets.
